rnatives: Part of our National Resource Fund will go toward transitioning Australia away from reliance on fossil fuels and toward a sustainable energy economy.</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>4. Prioritizing Australian Jobs & Communities</div><div><br></div><div>Too often, mining profits benefit corporate executives while leaving local communities struggling. The Emergence Party will:</div><div><br></div><div>Ensure Mining Companies Prioritize Local Jobs: Preference must be given to Australian workers rather than relying on overseas labor.</div><div><br></div><div>Invest in Regional Development: Mining regions will receive dedicated funding for infrastructure, healthcare, and education.</div><div><br></div><div>Support Workers in Transitioning Industries: As we shift toward renewables, we‚Äôll provide training and job opportunities for workers moving out of fossil fuel industries.</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>Why This Matters</div><div><br></div><div>The resources of this country belong to all Australians, not just those with corporate connections. We have the power to take back control of our wealth, ensuring that it serves the public interest rather than private profits.</div><div><br></div><div>Other countries have successfully taxed their natural resources and reinvested in their people. There is no reason Australia should settle for anything less.</div><div><br></div><div>A Call to Action</div><div><br></div><div>The Emergence Party is fighting for a future where Australia‚Äôs wealth benefits you, not billion-dollar corporations. It‚Äôs time to put the people first.</div><div><br></div><div>Join us in making this vision a reality. Learn more at wendellsdiary.com.</div>
